-- China’s Antibiotic Resistance Rate as High as 80%, Xinhua Says
-- B y   J o s h u a   F e l l m a n
-- 2012-03-22T15:50:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-22/china-s-antibiotic-resistance-rate-as-high-as-80-xinhua-says.html
China ’s antibiotic resistance rates
had risen as high as 80 percent fof some bacteria collected in
2010, Xinhua News Agency said, citing Lu yuan, head of Peking
University’s Institute of Clinical Pharmacology.  China’s resistance rate is higher than elsewhere, and the
government “has paid great atttention” to the use of
antibacterial drugs, the official news service reported. The
study took 270,000 samples from 128 hospitals, Xinhua said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
